President Uhuru Kenyatta recently presided over the African Women Leaders Network Leadership Retreat that was held at Safari Park Hotel, Nairobi. The three-day retreat, which saw women from all parts of African countries convey together unity, leadership and developments among the women. Former President of Malawi Joyce Banda said, “Ladies should learn to listen and remind yourselves that you cannot know it all since a person who learns to take advise from others becomes powerful.” The President urged women leaders to develop mechanisms that equip young men and women with appropriate skills, resources and opportunities. The African Women Leaders Network is a women’s led movement, launched in 2017 with the support of the African Union Commission and the United Nations.